sql:
SELECT recruitment_id, recruitment_count
FROM recruitment_data
WHERE recruitment_count > 500;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM recruitment_data
WHERE year_id > 2000;

SELECT deviation 
FROM deviations 
WHERE deviation_type = 'standard deviation';

SELECT recruitment_count 
FROM recruitment_data 
WHERE recruitment_id = 1;

external_knowledge:
- "seasons of time" refers to the different years;
- "echoes of new beginnings" metaphorically refers to the recruitment counts;
- "average voices of growth" represents the average recruitment count per year.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS total_users
FROM dataset_access
WHERE status = 'failed';

SELECT reports.report_type, data_approval.approval_status
FROM reports
INNER JOIN data_approval ON reports.request_id = data_approval.request_id;

SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM dataset_access
WHERE access_type = 'download' AND status = 'failed';

SELECT report_id, report_date
FROM reports
WHERE status = 'draft';

external_knowledge:
- "Golden keys" metaphorically refers to the report IDs;
- "Gateways" represents the request IDs;
- "Dates of dawn" metaphorically represents the report dates;
- "Nature of the scrolls" refers to the report types;
- "Whispers of difference" relates to the deviation values;
- "Scrolls that have seen the light of finality" means that the reports have a status of "final".
